MULTIPLE SELECTORS

selector 1, selector 2 {
    Task to Complete....
}


eg. <h1>Hello World</h1>
    <p>How are you today?</p>
    
   h1, p {
      color: red;
   }
   
   Hierarchical Selectors
   
   selector1 selector2 {
    ///no comma and must have space
    // parent(selector1) child(selector2)
   }
   
   eg. .container-fluid h1 {color: red;}
   
   div .container-fluid
      h1 #title
          Hello World
   
   ****IMPORTANT TO READ RIGHT TO LEFT 
     <--------
     div .title {color: red;}
     
    Combination selectors
    
    element_selector.class/Id_selector {color: red;}
    
    no space between element and class/Id
    
   *****READ LEFT TO RIGHT AND THEY MUST BE IN SAME ELEMENT
   
